.TH "WKS" "5" "Jan 01, 1980" "0.3.1" "wk"
.SH NAME
wks \- Which-Key source file for wk
.sp
wks is the scripting language used by \fBwk\fP(1) to define key chords.
This page is the complete reference. If you\(aqre new to wks, start with
the \fI\%getting started\fP guide and the
\fI\%examples\fP\&.
.SH GRAMMAR
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
key_chord          \-> ( chord | prefix | chord_array ) ;

chord              \-> trigger_key description keyword* ( command | meta_command ) ;

prefix             \-> trigger_key description keyword* \(aq{\(aq ( key_chord )+ \(aq}\(aq ;

chord_array        \-> ( implicit_array | explicit_array ) ;

implicit_array     \-> modifier* \(aq...\(aq description keyword* ( command | meta_command ) ;

explicit_array     \-> \(aq[\(aq ( trigger_key | chord_expression )+ \(aq]\(aq description keyword* ( command | meta_command ) ;

chord_expression   \-> \(aq(\(aq trigger_key description keyword* ( command | meta_command )? \(aq)\(aq ;

trigger_key        \-> modifier* ( normal_key | special_key | key_options ) ;

normal_key         \-> ( \(aq\e\e\(aq [\e\e\e[\e]{}#\(dq:^+()] | [^\es\e[\e]{}#\(dq:^+()] ) ;

special_key        \-> ( \(aqLeft\(aq    | \(aqRight\(aq   | \(aqUp\(aq     | \(aqDown\(aq | \(aqBS\(aq
                      | \(aqTAB\(aq     | \(aqSPC\(aq     | \(aqRET\(aq    | \(aqDEL\(aq  | \(aqESC\(aq
                      | \(aqHome\(aq    | \(aqPgUp\(aq    | \(aqPgDown\(aq | \(aqEnd\(aq  | \(aqBegin\(aq
                      | \(aqVolDown\(aq | \(aqVolMute\(aq | \(aqVolUp\(aq  | \(aqPlay\(aq | \(aqStop\(aq
                      | \(aqPrev\(aq    | \(aqNext\(aq    | \(aqF\(aq[1\-35] ) \es+ ;

modifier           \-> ( \(aqC\(aq | \(aqH\(aq | \(aqM\(aq | \(aqS\(aq ) \(aq\-\(aq ;

key_options        \-> \(aq<\(aq ( modifier* ( normal_key | special_key | \(aq...\(aq ) )+ \(aq>\(aq ;

description        \-> \(aq\(dq\(aq ( \(aq\e\e\(dq\(aq | [^\(dq] | interpolation )* \(aq\(dq\(aq ;

command            \-> \(aq%\(aq delimiter ( . | interpolation )* delimiter ;

delimiter          \-> ( open_delim | close_delim | ([^[{(])\e1 ) ;

open_delim         \-> ( \(aq{{\(aq | \(aq((\(aq | \(aq[[\(aq ) ;

close_delim        \-> ( \(aq}}\(aq | \(aq))\(aq | \(aq]]\(aq ) ;

interpolation      \-> \(aq%(\(aq ( chord_metadata | arg_position | user_variable ) \(aq)\(aq ;

chord_metadata     \-> ( \(aqkey\(aq
                      | \(aqindex\(aq
                      | \(aqindex+1\(aq
                      | \(aqdesc\(aq
                      | \(aqdesc^\(aq
                      | \(aqdesc^^\(aq
                      | \(aqdesc,\(aq
                      | \(aqdesc,,\(aq
                      | \(aqwrap_cmd\(aq );

arg_position       \-> \(aq$\(aq [0\-9]+ ;

user_variable      \-> [^)]+ ;

keyword            \-> ( hook | flag ) ;

meta_command       \-> \(aq@\(aq ( \(aqgoto\(aq description ) ;

hook               \-> \(aq^\(aq ( \(aqbefore\(aq
                          | \(aqafter\(aq
                          | \(aqsync\-before\(aq
                          | \(aqsync\-after\(aq ) command ;

flag               \-> \(aq+\(aq ( \(aqkeep\(aq
                          | \(aqclose\(aq
                          | \(aqinherit\(aq
                          | \(aqignore\(aq
                          | \(aqunhook\(aq
                          | \(aqdeflag\(aq
                          | \(aqno\-before\(aq
                          | \(aqno\-after\(aq
                          | \(aqwrite\(aq
                          | \(aqexecute\(aq
                          | \(aqsync\-command\(aq
                          | \(aqunwrap\(aq
                          | \(aqwrap\(aq \(aq\(dq\(aq ( \(aq\e\e\(dq\(aq | [^\(dq] | interpolation )* \(aq\(dq\(aq
                          | \(aqtitle\(aq ( \(aq\(dq\(aq ( \(aq\e\e\(dq\(aq | [^\(dq] | interpolation )* \(aq\(dq\(aq )?
                          | \(aqargs\(aq ( \(aq\(dq\(aq ( \(aq\e\e\(dq\(aq | [^\(dq] | interpolation )* \(aq\(dq\(aq )+ ) ;

preprocessor_macro \-> \(aq:\(aq ( string_macro
                          | switch_macro
                          | integer_macro
                          | unsigned_macro
                          | number_macro ) ;

string_macro       \-> ( \(aqinclude\(aq
                      | \(aqfg\(aq
                      | \(aqfg\-key\(aq
                      | \(aqfg\-delimiter\(aq
                      | \(aqfg\-prefix\(aq
                      | \(aqfg\-chord\(aq
                      | \(aqfg\-title\(aq
                      | \(aqfg\-goto\(aq
                      | \(aqbg\(aq
                      | \(aqbd\(aq
                      | \(aqshell\(aq
                      | \(aqfont\(aq
                      | \(aqtitle\(aq
                      | \(aqtitle\-font\(aq
                      | \(aqdelimiter\(aq
                      | \(aqwrap\-cmd\(aq
                      | \(aqvar\(aq \(aq\(dq\(aq ( \(aq\e\e\(dq\(aq | [^\(dq] | user_variable )* \(aq\(dq\(aq ) \(aq\(dq\(aq ( \(aq\e\e\(dq\(aq | [^\(dq] | user_variable )* \(aq\(dq\(aq ;

switch_macro       \-> ( \(aqdebug\(aq
                      | \(aqunsorted\(aq
                      | \(aqtop\(aq
                      | \(aqbottom\(aq );

integer_macro      \-> ( \(aqmenu\-width\(aq
                      | \(aqmenu\-gap\(aq
                      | \(aqtable\-padding\(aq ) \(aq\-\(aq? [0\-9]+ ;

unsigned_macro     \-> ( \(aqmax\-columns\(aq
                      | \(aqborder\-width\(aq
                      | \(aqwidth\-padding\(aq
                      | \(aqheight\-padding\(aq
                      | \(aqdelay\(aq
                      | \(aqkeep\-delay\(aq ) [0\-9]+ ;

number_macro       \-> ( \(aqborder\-radius\(aq ) \(aq\-\(aq? [0\-9]+ ( \(aq.\(aq [0\-9]* )? ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Comments begin with \fB#\fP and extend to the end of the line. The \fB#\fP
character is literal inside descriptions and commands; it
does not need to be escaped.
.SH TRIGGER KEYS
.sp
A trigger key is the keypress that activates a chord.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
trigger_key \-> modifier* ( normal_key | special_key | key_options ) ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Normal Keys
.sp
Any printable, non\-whitespace, UTF\-8 character.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
normal_key \-> ( \(aq\e\e\(aq [\e\e\e[\e]{}#\(dq:^+()] | [^\es\e[\e]{}#\(dq:^+()] ) ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
