T}
.TE
.sp
To match \fBControl+c\fP, write \fBC\-c\fP\&. Modifiers chain: \fBC\-M\-x\fP matches
\fBControl+Alt+x\fP\&.
.sp
\fBNOTE:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The Shift modifier (\fBS\-\fP) has a subtlety with normal keys. If pressing
a key with Shift produces a different character (e.g., \fBa\fP → \fBA\fP), use
the shifted character directly \- \fBA\fP, not \fBS\-a\fP\&. The \fBS\-\fP modifier is
only needed for keys where Shift does not change the output (e.g.,
special keys like \fBS\-TAB\fP).
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Key Options
.sp
Key options let a chord bind to the \fBfirst available\fP key from a
list.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
key_options \-> \(aq<\(aq ( modifier* ( normal_key | special_key | \(aq...\(aq ) )+ \(aq>\(aq ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
<s i g> \(dqSignal\(dq %{{signal}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
The parser tries \fBs\fP first; if already bound, it tries \fBi\fP, then \fBg\fP\&.
If all keys are taken, an error is raised. The ellipsis (\fB\&...\fP)
expands to the implicit array keys as a fallback:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
<s i g ...> \(dqSignal\(dq %{{signal}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Modifiers before \fB<\fP apply to all options. Modifiers inside apply to
individual keys:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
M\-<a b>      # Both options get M\-
<a M\-b>      # Only \(aqb\(aq gets M\-

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Key options are most useful with \fI\%:include\fP to avoid
trigger key collisions across files. See the \fI\%key options
example\fP\&.
.SH DESCRIPTIONS
.sp
A description is a quoted string shown as the hint text in the menu.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
description \-> \(aq\(dq\(aq ( \(aq\e\e\(dq\(aq | [^\(dq] | interpolation )* \(aq\(dq\(aq ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Descriptions can contain \fI\%interpolations\fP\&. Use \fB\e\(dq\fP
for a literal double quote. An empty description (\fB\(dq\(dq\fP) is valid.
.SH COMMANDS
.sp
A command is the action executed when a chord completes.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
command \-> \(aq%\(aq delimiter ( . | interpolation )* delimiter ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
A command starts with \fB%\fP followed by a delimiter pair. Anything
between the delimiters is passed to the shell. If it runs in your
terminal, it works in a wks command.
.SS Delimiters
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
delimiter   \-> ( open_delim | close_delim | ([^[{(])\e1 ) ;
open_delim  \-> ( \(aq{{\(aq | \(aq((\(aq | \(aq[[\(aq ) ;
close_delim \-> ( \(aq}}\(aq | \(aq))\(aq | \(aq]]\(aq ) ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
The three bracket\-style delimiters have matching open/close pairs.
Any other ASCII character repeated twice also works as a delimiter:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
%{{echo \(dqhello\(dq}}           # Standard
%((echo \(dqhello\(dq))           # Parentheses
%[[echo \(dqhello\(dq]]           # Brackets
%||echo \(dqhello\(dq||           # Arbitrary

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
This flexibility, inspired by \fBsed\fP(1), means your command content
never conflicts with the delimiter \- just pick one that doesn\(aqt appear
in the command. Different chords can use different delimiters.
.SH CHORDS
.sp
A chord is a complete key binding \- pressing its trigger key performs
an action.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
chord \-> trigger_key description keyword* ( command | meta_command ) ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
b \(dqBrave\(dq %{{brave}}
C\-s \(dqSave\(dq %{{save\-file}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH PREFIXES
.sp
A prefix groups related chords under a common trigger key. Pressing
the prefix key opens a submenu rather than executing a command.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
prefix \-> trigger_key description keyword* \(aq{\(aq ( key_chord )+ \(aq}\(aq ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Prefixes can be nested arbitrarily deep:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
e \(dqEmacs\(dq
{
    o \(dqOpen\(dq %{{emacs}}
    r \(dqRoam\(dq
    {
        h \(dqHome\(dq %{{emacs ~/Documents/roam/home.org}}
        j \(dqJournal\(dq %{{emacs ~/Documents/roam/daily}}
    }
}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH CHORD ARRAYS
.sp
Chord arrays generate multiple chords from a shared template, reducing
repetition.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
chord_array \-> ( implicit_array | explicit_array ) ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Implicit Arrays
.sp
An implicit array uses the predefined implicit array keys (set via
\fB\-\-implicit\-keys\fP or \fB:implicit\-array\-keys\fP) as trigger keys.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
implicit_array \-> modifier* \(aq...\(aq description keyword* command ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Implicit]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
\&... \(dqWorkspace %(index+1)\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace %(index)}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Expanded]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
# Assuming implicit keys are \(dqasdfghjkl;\(dq
a \(dqWorkspace 1\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 0}}
s \(dqWorkspace 2\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 1}}
d \(dqWorkspace 3\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 2}}
# ... and so on for each implicit key

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Explicit Arrays
.sp
An explicit array lists its trigger keys between brackets.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
explicit_array \-> \(aq[\(aq ( trigger_key | chord_expression )+ \(aq]\(aq description keyword* command ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Array]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
[asdfghjkl] \(dqWorkspace %(index+1)\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace %(index)}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Expanded]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
a \(dqWorkspace 1\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 0}}
s \(dqWorkspace 2\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 1}}
d \(dqWorkspace 3\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 2}}
f \(dqWorkspace 4\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 3}}
g \(dqWorkspace 5\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 4}}
h \(dqWorkspace 6\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 5}}
j \(dqWorkspace 7\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 6}}
k \(dqWorkspace 8\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 7}}
l \(dqWorkspace 9\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 8}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Chord Expressions
.sp
A chord expression customizes an individual entry within a chord
array. Wrap it in parentheses inside the brackets. Only a trigger key
and description are required \- any missing command or keywords are
filled in by the surrounding array.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
chord_expression \-> \(aq(\(aq trigger_key description keyword* command? \(aq)\(aq ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Expressive]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
[
    (b \(dqBrave\(dq)
    (c \(dqMullvad Chrome\(dq %{{mullvad\-exclude chrome ~/startpage.html}})
    x
] \(dqXDG\-OPEN\(dq %{{%(desc,,) ~/startpage.html}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Expanded]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
b \(dqBrave\(dq %{{brave ~/startpage.html}}
c \(dqMullvad Chrome\(dq %{{mullvad\-exclude chrome ~/startpage.html}}
x \(dqXDG\-OPEN\(dq %{{xdg\-open ~/startpage.html}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Here, \fBb\fP and \fBx\fP inherit the array\(aqs command template, while \fBc\fP
provides its own. The \fBx\fP key has no expression, so it also inherits
the array\(aqs description.
.SH INTERPOLATIONS
.sp
An interpolation inserts dynamic values into descriptions and
commands.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
interpolation \-> \(aq%(\(aq ( chord_metadata | arg_position | user_variable ) \(aq)\(aq ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
There are three kinds:
.SS Chord Metadata
.sp
Built\-in identifiers that reference properties of the current chord.
Valid in descriptions and commands.
.TS
box center;
l|l.
T{
Identifier
T}	T{
Value
T}
_
T{
\fB%(key)\fP
T}	T{
The trigger key of the current chord
T}
_
T{
\fB%(index)\fP
T}	T{
0\-based position in parse order within the current scope
T}
_
T{
\fB%(index+1)\fP
T}	T{
1\-based position (same as above, offset by one)
T}
_
T{
\fB%(desc)\fP
T}	T{
The description (not valid inside a description)
T}
_
T{
\fB%(desc^)\fP
T}	T{
Description with first character capitalized
T}
_
T{
\fB%(desc^^)\fP
T}	T{
Description fully uppercased
T}
_
T{
\fB%(desc,)\fP
T}	T{
Description with first character lowercased
T}
_
T{
\fB%(desc,,)\fP
T}	T{
Description fully lowercased
T}
_
T{
\fB%(wrap_cmd)\fP
T}	T{
The global wrap command value
T}
.TE
.sp
\fBNOTE:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
Index values are resolved \fBbefore\fP sorting. \fB%(index)\fP reflects
parse order, not the final display order. Prefixes start a new scope
for their children.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS User Variables
.sp
Variables defined with the \fI\%:var macro\fP\&. Valid in
descriptions, commands, and preprocessor macro arguments.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
user_variable \-> [^)]+ ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
:var \(dqCMD\(dq \(dqhyprctl dispatch workspace\(dq
[asdfghjkl] \(dqWorkspace %(index+1)\(dq %{{%(CMD) %(index)}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Argument Positions
.sp
Positional references to values defined with \fB+args\fP\&. Valid in
descriptions and commands where \fB+args\fP is defined.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
arg_position \-> \(aq$\(aq [0\-9]+ ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fB%($0)\fP is the first argument, \fB%($1)\fP the second, and so on.
Undefined positions resolve to an empty string.
.sp
Arguments follow lexical scoping \- descendants within a prefix can
access that prefix\(aqs arguments. When a descendant defines its own
\fB+args\fP, its values shadow ancestor arguments at the same index, but
other indices remain accessible:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
p \(dq+Prefix\(dq +args \(dqouter0\(dq \(dqouter1\(dq
{
    a \(dqUse both\(dq +write %{{%($0) %($1)}}
    n \(dq+Nested\(dq +args \(dqinner0\(dq
    {
        # %($0) = \(dqinner0\(dq (shadowed), %($1) = \(dqouter1\(dq (inherited)
        b \(dqMixed\(dq +write %{{%($0) %($1)}}
    }
}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH HOOKS
.sp
Hooks attach additional commands to a chord or prefix.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
hook \-> \(aq^\(aq ( \(aqbefore\(aq | \(aqafter\(aq | \(aqsync\-before\(aq | \(aqsync\-after\(aq ) command ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
\fB^before\fP / \fB^after\fP
Run a command before or after the chord\(aqs own command, asynchronously.
.TP
\fB^sync\-before\fP / \fB^sync\-after\fP
Same, but block wk until the hook completes.
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBWARNING:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
A blocking \fBsync\-*\fP hook that never returns will freeze wk. You may
need to restart your system to regain keyboard control.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Hooks on a prefix apply to all direct child chords but \fBnot\fP to
nested prefixes (see \fI\%Inheritance\fP). Use \fB+unhook\fP,
\fB+no\-before\fP, or \fB+no\-after\fP on individual chords to opt out:
[Hooked]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
e \(dqEmacs\(dq ^before %{{switch\-to\-workspace 1}}
{
    o \(dqOpen\(dq %{{emacs}}
    r \(dqRoam\(dq %{{emacs ~/Documents/roam}}
    s \(dqScratch\(dq +unhook %{{emacs \-\-eval \(dq(scratch\-buffer)\(dq}}
}
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Equivalent]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
e \(dqEmacs\(dq
{
    o \(dqOpen\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 1; emacs}}
    r \(dqRoam\(dq %{{switch\-to\-workspace 1; emacs ~/Documents/roam}}
    s \(dqScratch\(dq %{{emacs \-\-eval \(dq(scratch\-buffer)\(dq}}
}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH FLAGS
.sp
Flags modify the behavior of a chord or prefix.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
flag \-> \(aq+\(aq ( \(aqkeep\(aq | \(aqclose\(aq | \(aqinherit\(aq | \(aqignore\(aq | \(aqunhook\(aq
            | \(aqdeflag\(aq | \(aqno\-before\(aq | \(aqno\-after\(aq | \(aqwrite\(aq
            | \(aqexecute\(aq | \(aqsync\-command\(aq | \(aqunwrap\(aq
            | \(aqwrap\(aq description | \(aqtitle\(aq description?
            | \(aqargs\(aq description+ ) ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Menu Control
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
\fB+keep\fP
Keep the menu open after executing the chord. Turns wk into a
\(dqhydra\(dq for repeated actions.
.TP
\fB+close\fP
Force\-close the menu. Useful to override \fB+keep\fP on the enclosing
prefix for specific chords.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
m \(dqMusic\(dq +keep
{
    n \(dqNext\(dq %{{mpc next}}
    p \(dqPrev\(dq %{{mpc prev}}
    o \(dqOpen player\(dq +close %{{kitty \-e ncmpcpp}}
}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Output Control
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
\fB+write\fP
Print the command text to stdout instead of executing it. Turns wk
into a selection prompt, like dmenu.
.TP
\fB+execute\fP
Execute the command normally. Overrides \fB+write\fP inherited from a
parent prefix.
.TP
\fB+sync\-command\fP
Execute the command synchronously (blocking). See the warning in
\fI\%Hooks\fP about blocking commands.
.UNINDENT
.SS Inheritance Control
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
\fB+inherit\fP
Force a nested prefix to inherit hooks and flags from its parent.
Has no effect on chords.
.TP
\fB+ignore\fP
Ignore all inherited hooks and flags. Has no effect on prefixes.
.TP
\fB+unhook\fP
Ignore all inherited hooks only.
.TP
\fB+deflag\fP
Ignore all inherited flags only.
.TP
\fB+no\-before\fP
Ignore inherited \fB^before\fP and \fB^sync\-before\fP hooks.
.TP
\fB+no\-after\fP
Ignore inherited \fB^after\fP and \fB^sync\-after\fP hooks.
.UNINDENT
.SS Command Wrapping
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
\fB+wrap\fP \fB\(dqwrapper\(dq\fP
Wrap this chord\(aqs command (or all commands in a prefix) with the
given string. The command is executed as \fB/bin/sh \-c \(dqWRAPPER CMD\(dq\fP\&.
Supports interpolation.
.TP
\fB+unwrap\fP
Prevent wrapping, even if a global wrap or inherited \fB+wrap\fP is set.
.UNINDENT
.sp
Wrap precedence, most specific to least:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP 1. 3
\fB+unwrap\fP on chord (no wrap)
.IP 2. 3
\fB+wrap \(dqcustom\(dq\fP on chord
.IP 3. 3
\fB+wrap\fP inherited from parent prefix
.IP 4. 3
Global \fB:wrap\-cmd\fP / \fB\-\-wrap\-cmd\fP
.IP 5. 3
No wrapper
.UNINDENT
[Wrapped]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
:wrap\-cmd \(dquwsm\-app \-\-\(dq
a \(dqApps\(dq
{
    b \(dqBrave\(dq %{{brave}}
}
f \(dqFoot\(dq +wrap \(dqfoot \-e\(dq
{
    n \(dqncmpcpp\(dq %{{ncmpcpp}}
}
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Equivalent]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
a \(dqApps\(dq
{
    b \(dqBrave\(dq %{{uwsm\-app \-\- brave}}
}
f \(dqFoot\(dq
{
    n \(dqncmpcpp\(dq %{{foot \-e ncmpcpp}}
}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Title
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
\fB+title\fP \fB\(dqtext\(dq\fP
Set a title displayed above the menu for this chord or prefix.
Supports interpolation. Overrides the global \fB\-\-title\fP setting.
An empty string (\fB\(dq\(dq\fP) clears any inherited or global title.
Omitting the argument sets the title to the chord\(aqs description.
.UNINDENT
.SS Arguments
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
\fB+args\fP \fB\(dqarg0\(dq\fP \fB\(dqarg1\(dq\fP ...
Define positional arguments accessible via \fB%($0)\fP, \fB%($1)\fP, etc.
See \fI\%Argument Positions\fP for scoping rules.
.UNINDENT
[Dynamic]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
[
    (a \(dqAlice\(dq +args \(dqalice@example.com\(dq)
    (b \(dqBob\(dq +args \(dqbob@example.com\(dq)
    c
] \(dqEmail %($0)\(dq +args \(dq(default)\(dq %{{mailto:%($0)}}
# a \-> mailto:alice@example.com
# b \-> mailto:bob@example.com
# c \-> mailto:(default)

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Static]
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
a \(dqAlice\(dq %{{mailto:alice@example.com}}
b \(dqBob\(dq %{{mailto:bob@example.com}}
c \(dqEmail (default)\(dq %{{mailto:(default)}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH META COMMANDS
.sp
A meta command controls wk\(aqs menu rather than running a shell command.
Meta commands are mutually exclusive with hooks and regular commands.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
meta_command \-> \(aq@\(aq ( \(aqgoto\(aq description ) ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS @goto
.sp
Navigates to a different location in the key chord hierarchy without
closing and restarting wk. The argument uses the same syntax as
\fB\-\-press\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fB@goto \(dq\(dq\fP \- navigate to the root menu
.IP \(bu 2
\fB@goto \(dqw\(dq\fP \- navigate to the \(dqw\(dq prefix
.IP \(bu 2
\fB@goto \(dqw m\(dq\fP \- navigate through \(dqw\(dq then \(dqm\(dq
.UNINDENT
.sp
If the path leads to a chord (not a prefix), that chord\(aqs command is
executed.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
w \(dqWindow\(dq +keep
{
    m \(dqMove\(dq +keep
    {
        ... \(dqMove to %(index+1)\(dq %{{move\-window %(index)}}
        BS \(dqGo back\(dq @goto \(dqw\(dq
        S\-BS \(dqGo home\(dq @goto \(dq\(dq
    }
    r \(dqResize\(dq +keep +inherit
    {
        ... \(dqResize %(index+1)\(dq %{{resize\-window %(index)}}
    }
}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBNOTE:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
\fB@goto\fP cannot be combined with hooks or commands. Circular goto
chains (e.g., \fBa @goto \(dqb\(dq\fP and \fBb @goto \(dqa\(dq\fP) are detected at
runtime and produce an error.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH PREPROCESSOR MACROS
.sp
Preprocessor macros configure the menu appearance and behavior, or
include other wks files. They start with \fB:\fP and override the
equivalent \fBwk\fP(1) command\-line flags.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
preprocessor_macro \-> \(aq:\(aq ( string_macro | switch_macro
                          | integer_macro | unsigned_macro
                          | number_macro ) ;

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
