.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SS Include Macro
.sp
The \fB:include\fP macro inserts the contents of another wks file,
similar to C\(aqs \fB#include\fP\&. Relative paths resolve from the directory
of the file being processed.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
b \(dqBrowser\(dq { :include \(dqbrowser.wks\(dq }
e \(dqEmacs\(dq ^before %{{switch\-to\-workspace 1}} { :include \(dqemacs.wks\(dq }

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBNOTE:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
Self\-includes and recursive includes produce an error. The same file
may be included multiple times. Unlike C\(aqs \fB#include\fP, the \fB:include\fP
macro can appear anywhere \- even mid\-description (though you probably
shouldn\(aqt).
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
See the \fI\%modular configs example\fP\&.
.SS Var Macro
.sp
The \fB:var\fP macro defines a variable for use in descriptions, commands,
and other preprocessor arguments. It takes two string arguments: a
name and a value.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
:var \(dqCMD\(dq \(dqhyprctl dispatch workspace\(dq
[asdfghjkl] \(dqWorkspace %(index+1)\(dq %{{%(CMD) %(index)}}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Setting the value to an empty string (\fB\(dq\(dq\fP) unsets the variable. The
variable name can contain any character except \fB)\fP and cannot shadow
built\-in chord metadata identifiers.
.sp
Both name and value support variable interpolation, enabling
\fBmeta\-variables\fP (variables with computed names) and \fBchained
references\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
# Meta\-variable: name computed from another variable
:var \(dqkey\(dq \(dqGREETING\(dq
:var \(dq%(key)\(dq \(dqHello, World!\(dq
a \(dqSay hello\(dq %{{echo %(GREETING)}}

# Chained references
:var \(dqhome\(dq \(dq/home/user\(dq
:var \(dqconfig\(dq \(dq%(home)/.config/wk\(dq

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Variables are resolved at definition time in a single pass \- define
them before use.
.sp
A common pattern is combining \fB:var\fP with \fB:include\fP for
environment\-specific configs:
[Hyprland]
.sp
\fB~/hyprland.wks\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
:var \(dqWORKSPACE_CMD\(dq \(dqhyprctl dispatch workspace\(dq
:include \(dqmain.wks\(dq
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[dwm]
.sp
\fB~/dwm.wks\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
:var \(dqWORKSPACE_CMD\(dq \(dqxdotool set_desktop\(dq
:include \(dqmain.wks\(dq
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
[Shared]
.sp
\fB~/main.wks\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
w \(dqWorkspace\(dq
{
    [asdfghjkl] \(dq%(index+1)\(dq %{{%(WORKSPACE_CMD) %(index)}}
}
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
See the \fI\%variables example\fP\&.
