.SH INHERITANCE
.sp
Hooks and flags on a prefix are inherited by its direct child chords,
but \fBnot\fP by nested prefixes. Use \fB+inherit\fP to opt a nested prefix
in, or use the negation flags (\fB+unhook\fP, \fB+deflag\fP, \fB+ignore\fP,
\fB+no\-before\fP, \fB+no\-after\fP) to opt individual chords out.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
a \(dqPrefix\(dq +write
{
    w \(dqWritten\(dq %{{I get written!}}
    n \(dqNested\(dq
    {
        r \(dqRuns\(dq %{{echo \(dqI get run!\(dq}}
    }
}
# a w \-> prints \(dqI get written!\(dq to stdout
# a n r \-> executes echo \(dqI get run!\(dq

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
To make the nested prefix inherit:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
a \(dqPrefix\(dq +write
{
    w \(dqWritten\(dq %{{I get written!}}
    n \(dqNested\(dq +inherit
    {
        r \(dqAlso written\(dq %{{I also get written!}}
    }
}

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH SORTING
.sp
Key chords are sorted alphabetically by default. Index interpolations
are resolved \fBbefore\fP sorting, so \fB%(index)\fP reflects parse order,
not display order.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
[neio] \(dqSwitch %(index+1)\(dq %{{xdotool set_desktop %(index)}}
b \(dqSecond\(dq +write %{{%(index)}}
a \(dqFirst\(dq +write %{{%(index)}}

# Display order (sorted): a, b, e, i, n, o
# But: a\(aqs command is %{{5}}, b\(aqs is %{{4}}, n\(aqs is %{{0}}, etc.

.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Disable sorting with \fB\-\-unsorted\fP or \fB:unsorted\fP\&.
